Two suspects were arrested following a 20 minute long high
speed chase in Ekurhuleni. On Tuesday 31 May 2022, the Ekurhuleni Metro Police Department
(EMPD) Specialised Task Team Officers (STT), arrested two (2) fleeing suspects
and suspicious items, were uncovered. EMPD spokesperson, Kelebogile Thepa said, “The eye hawked
EMPD Officers on crime prevention operation, patrolling the stretch of N3 freeway,
received a look-out on the two-way radio, about a robbed/hijacked silver Toyota
Fortuner Special Utility Vehicle (SUV), reported to be approaching the N3
freeway, from Modderfontein side.”  She said not long, the speeding SUV fitting the description,
was spotted on the N3 expressway with two (2) male occupants, with no intentions,
to stop. Officers called for back-up, as they failed on an attempt, to halt the
Toyota. “Other Law Enforcers and private security company’s
responded and the chase ensued, while the SUV driven recklessly and negligently,
drove into few motor-vehicles, leaving them behind with huge damages. “After a good 20 minutes’ chase, the Toyota Fortuner
displaying false registration/number plates, was cornered with two (2)
occupants, who are 29 and 49-years of age, in Thokoza area by the Serema
street.” She said the SUV was thoroughly searched and Officers
uncovered implements used in stealing vehicles, a high calibre jammer device
and few car keys with immobilisers. The handcuffed pair, is facing charges of failing to stop
when instructed by Officers in uniform, possession of vehicle breaking
implements, possession of suspected stolen vehicle added is reckless and
negligent driving. They are expected to appear, in the Palmridge Magistrate’s
Court soon